VALUES
(43, 8, 7, 58, 4, 12, 13, 'He that is without sin among you', 'Judgment and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and accountability in both passages. John 8:7 emphasizes the need for self-reflection before casting judgment, while Hebrews 4:12-13 speaks to the discernment of thoughts and intentions, revealing that all are accountable before God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 9, 21, 7, 22, 22, 'convicted by their own conscience', 'Conscience and Self-Reflection', 'This connection highlights the theme of self-awareness and conviction in both passages. In John 8:9, the individuals leave after being ''convicted by their own conscience,'' while Ecclesiastes 7:22 emphasizes that one''s heart knows their own faults, suggesting a shared focus on personal accountability.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 9, 45, 2, 15, 15, 'convicted by their own conscience', 'Conscience and Conviction Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of conscience in both passages. In John 8:9, the individuals are convicted by their own conscience, while Romans 2:15 discusses how conscience bears witness to the law written in their hearts.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 9, 62, 3, 20, 20, 'convicted by their own conscience', 'Conscience and Heart Condemnation', 'This connection highlights the theme of internal conviction, as both passages address the role of conscience and heart in judgment. In John 8:9, those present are ''convicted by their own conscience,'' while 1 John 3:20 speaks of the heart condemning us.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 9, 1, 42, 21, 22, 'convicted by their own conscience', 'Guilt and Conscience', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of guilt and the resulting conviction of conscience. In John, the accusers leave one by one, indicating their awareness of their own wrongdoing, while in Genesis, the brothers acknowledge their guilt regarding Joseph''s suffering.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 9, 18, 5, 12, 13, 'being convicted by their own conscience', 'Conviction and Craftiness', 'This connection highlights the theme of being convicted by one''s own conscience, as seen in John 8:9, which parallels Job 5:12-13''s idea of the wise being taken in their own craftiness. Both passages emphasize the consequences of one''s actions and intentions.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 9, 19, 71, 13, 13, 'being convicted by their own conscience', 'Conviction and Adversaries', 'This connection highlights the theme of being confronted by one''s own conscience and the adversaries that seek to harm. Both passages reflect a struggle against those who oppose or seek to condemn, emphasizing the internal conflict and external reproach faced by individuals.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 9, 43, 8, 10, 10, NULL, 'Jesus and the Accuser''s Absence', 'This connection highlights the transition from the crowd''s departure to the woman''s encounter with Jesus. The absence of her accusers sets the stage for Jesus to address her directly, emphasizing her situation of being uncondemned.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 10, 23, 41, 11, 12, 'hath no man condemned thee', 'Shame and Accusation', 'This connection highlights the theme of shame and the absence of accusers. In both passages, the idea of those who contend or accuse being rendered as nothing is present.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 11, 43, 3, 17, 17, 'Neither do I condemn thee', 'Condemnation and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the absence of condemnation. Jesus'' statement in John 8:11 reflects his mission in John 3:17, where he clarifies that he was not sent to condemn but to save.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 11, 43, 5, 14, 14, 'sin no more', 'Connection of Sin and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the command to ''sin no more'' following an act of mercy. This connection highlights the relationship between forgiveness and the call to righteous living.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 11, 23, 1, 16, 18, 'go, and sin no more', 'Forgiveness and Cleansing from Sin', 'This connection highlights the theme of forgiveness and the call to cease sinning. Both passages emphasize the importance of making oneself clean and turning away from evil actions.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 11, 42, 15, 7, 7, 'Neither do I condemn thee', 'Repentance and Forgiveness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of forgiveness and the joy of repentance. In both passages, Jesus emphasizes the importance of not condemning sinners and the joy in heaven when one repents.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 11, 42, 5, 32, 32, 'go, and sin no more', 'Jesus'' Call to Repentance', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' mission to offer forgiveness and encourage repentance. Both passages emphasize His compassion towards sinners and the call to change one''s life.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 11, 18, 34, 31, 31, 'go, and sin no more', 'Forgiveness and Transformation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of repentance and the call to avoid sin after receiving forgiveness. In John, Jesus instructs the woman to ''go, and sin no more,'' while in Job, the speaker expresses a commitment to not offend God again after chastisement.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 11, 20, 28, 13, 13, 'neither do I condemn thee', 'Mercy and Forgiveness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of acknowledging sin and the mercy that follows. John 8:11 highlights Jesus'' forgiveness, while Proverbs 28:13 underscores the necessity of confessing and forsaking sin to receive mercy.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 43, 9, 5, 5, 'I am the light of the world', 'Light of the World Connection', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus as ''the light of the world.'' This connection highlights the continuity of Jesus'' identity and mission in bringing illumination to those who follow him.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 43, 12, 46, 46, 'light of the world', 'Light and Darkness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus as the light of the world, indicating that belief in Him leads to freedom from darkness. This connection highlights the transformative power of following Jesus, as both verses affirm that believers will not abide in darkness.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 40, 5, 14, 14, 'light of the world', 'Light of the World Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''the light of the world.'' John 8:12 presents Jesus as the source of light, while Matthew 5:14 extends this idea to his followers, indicating their role in reflecting that light.', 'theme', 0.825, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 18, 33, 28, 28, NULL, 'Light and Deliverance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of light as a source of life and deliverance. John 8:12 speaks of Jesus as the light of the world, while Job 33:28 mentions seeing the light as a form of salvation from the pit.', 'theme', 0.748, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 19, 18, 28, 28, 'light of the world', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light overcoming darkness. John 8:12 speaks of Jesus as the light of the world, while Psalms 18:28 highlights God''s role in enlightening darkness.', 'theme', 0.734, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 23, 9, 2, 2, 'light of the world', 'Light in Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light overcoming darkness. John 8:12 declares Jesus as ''the light of the world,'' while Isaiah 9:2 speaks of a great light shining on those in darkness.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 23, 60, 1, 3, 'light of the world', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light overcoming darkness. John 8:12 speaks of Jesus as the light of the world, while Isaiah 60:1-3 describes the glory of the Lord arising amidst darkness. This connection highlights the transformative power of divine light.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 13, 43, 5, 31, 47, 'Thou bearest record of thyself', 'Witness and Testimony Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the validity of witness and testimony. In John 8:13, the Pharisees challenge Jesus'' self-testimony, while John 5:31-47 discusses the necessity of external witnesses to affirm his claims.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 14, 43, 13, 3, 3, 'whence I came, and whither I go', 'Connection of Origin and Destination', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' awareness of his origin and destination. In John 8:14, Jesus states he knows ''whence I came, and whither I go,'' while John 13:3 confirms he ''was come from God, and went to God.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 14, 43, 16, 28, 28, 'I know whence I came, and whither I go', 'Connection of Origin and Destination', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' awareness of his origin and destination. In John 8:14, he states, ''I know whence I came, and whither I go,'' which parallels John 16:28''s declaration of coming forth from the Father and returning to Him.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 14, 4, 12, 3, 3, NULL, 'Meekness and True Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of true understanding and humility. Jesus asserts his knowledge of his origins and destination, paralleling Moses'' meekness, which reflects a deep understanding of his role and purpose.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 14, 16, 5, 14, 19, 'whence I came, and whither I go', 'Leadership and Responsibility', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowing one''s origins and responsibilities. Jesus speaks of knowing ''whence I came, and whither I go,'' while Nehemiah demonstrates his awareness of his role and the burdens of the people he leads.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 14, 47, 11, 31, 31, 'my record is true', 'Truth and Divine Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of truth and knowledge. Jesus asserts the truth of his origin and destination, while Paul appeals to God''s knowledge of his honesty.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 14, 47, 12, 11, 11, 'I know whence I came', 'Self-Identification and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of self-assertion and authority. Both passages emphasize the speaker''s confidence in their identity and position, with Jesus asserting his true knowledge of his origins and Paul defending his apostolic status.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
